Enum Utilities.Effects.Particle

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Utilities.Effects.Particle>
      • me.pagekite.glen3b.library.bukkit.Utilities.Effects.Particle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Utilities.Effects.Particle>
    Enclosing class:
    Utilities.Effects

    public static enum Utilities.Effects.Particle
extends java.lang.Enum<Utilities.Effects.Particle>

    ParticleEffects Library v1.4


    This library was created by DarkBladee12 based on content related to particles of microgeek (names and packet values). It allows you to display all known Minecraft particle effects on a CraftBukkit server.

    You are welcome to use it, modify it and redistribute it under the following conditions:

    1. Don't claim this class as your own
    2. Don't remove this text
    (Would be nice if you provide credit to me)

    Note that the enum values of this class do not include icon crack, block dust, or block crack particles, as they are treated specially.

    Author:
    DarkBladee12, microgeek, Glen Husman (doucmentation fixes, overload improvements)

      • display

        public void display(Location center,
           double range,
           Vector offset,
           float speed,
           int amount)
        Displays a particle effect which is only visible for players within a certain range of the centerpoint.
        Parameters:
        center - The center location of the particle effect.
        range - The range which binds all players that will receive the packet.
        offset - A vector representing the maximum distance particles can fly away from the center location on each axis (independently).
        speed - "Speed" of the particles, a data value of sorts.
        amount - The number of particles to display.

      • display

        public void display(Location center,
           Vector offset,
           float speed,
           int amount)
        Displays a particle effect which is visible for all players who can hypothetically see the particle if the appropriate packet is sent to their client. The range is very generous, however larger values can be specified in the linked overload.
        Parameters:
        center - The center location of the particle effect.
        offset - A vector representing the maximum distance particles can fly away from the center location on each axis (independently).
        speed - "Speed" of the particles, a data value of sorts.
        amount - The number of particles to display.
        See Also:
        display(Location, double, Vector, float, int)

      • displayBlockCrack

        public static void displayBlockCrack(Location center,
                     double range,
                     MaterialData data,
                     Vector offset,
                     int amount)
        Displays a block break (block crack) particle effect which is only visible for players within a certain range of the centerpoint.
        Parameters:
        center - The center location of the particle effect.
        data - The material data (which includes type) of the represented block. This value may not be null.
        offset - A vector representing the maximum distance particles can fly away from the center location on each axis (independently).
        amount - The number of particles to display.
        range - The range which binds all players that will receive the packet.
